The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Child labour

 New Delhi, May 4: The International Labour Organi- sation reported today that the number of child labourers had come down the world over between 2000 and 2004 by 11 per cent, a drop from 246 to 218 million, says our correspondent.

 About India, child labour specialist Herve Berger said Andhra Pradesh was in the forefront of tackling the issue by establishing the fact that all non-school going children are categorised as child labourers. 




